steps.instruction:
### Making Dough
- In a large mixing bowl combine 3 cups of bread flour, 1 cup of oats, 2 tablespoons of butter, 1.5 teaspoons of salt, 3 tablespoons of honey, 2 teaspoons of instant yeast and 1.25 cups of lukewarm milk
- Mix together till a rough, shaggy dough forms
- Knead by hand or mixer (with dough hook), until its springy though still somewhat soft, about 5 to 7 minutes
    - If kneading by hand, knead on a greased work surface. this is because adding more dough will make it dry
- Place dough into a lightly greased bowl and allow to rise for 1 hour. 

### Shaping The Dough
- Transfer the dough to a lightly greased work surface. 
- Flatten the dough into a 6x8 inch rectangle
- Fold the top down to the center, pressing firmly with the heel of your hand
- Pull the upper left and right corners into the center and press to seal them 
- Repeat the first fold (folding down to the center) 3 to 4 more times till you get a 9 inch to 10 inch log
- Tuck the ends slightly, and turn the log over to the log over so its seam is on the bottom
![](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/sites/default/files/2020-02/step-5.gif)
- Place the log into a lightly greased 9x5 inch pan, and tent the pan with lightly greased plastic wrap
- Let rise for 1 to 1.5 hours or until it creased about 1 inch over the rim of the pan
- Near the end of the rise preheat your oven to 350F

### Baking
- Uncover the risen loaf
- Beat the egg white with the cold water
- Brush the top of the loaf with the beaten egg
- Sprinkle oats on the top
- Bake the bread for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown
    - If the bread is browning too quickly, cover with foil for the last 10 minutes 
- Let the bread reach room temperature before slicing
